==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semiglutin
<hw>Sem`i*glu"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A peptonelike body, insoluble in alcohol, formed by
boiling collagen or gelatin for a long time in water.
<xex>Hemicollin</xex>, a like body, is also formed at the same time, and
differs from semiglutin by being partly soluble in alcohol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semihistorical</ent>⟦br⟧
